<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5361.3.5>
    dc:creator "Koreeda, Reo", "Maeda, Ken", "Motomura, Hiroyuki" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "A new subtropical species of goby of the genus Luciogobius (Gobiidae) from southwestern Japan" ;
    bibo:endPage "408" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-11-02" ;
    bibo:startPage "390" ;
    bibo:volume "5361" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144866>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144868>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144870>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144872>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144874>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144876>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144878>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144880>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144882>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144884> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144866>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Fresh specimens of Luciogobius griseus n. sp. from Amami-oshima island (A: holotype; KAUM–I. 144559, male, 38.8 mm SL), Yaku-shima island (B: KAUM–I. 163253, female, 34.3 mm SL), Tokuno-shima island (C: KAUM–I. 144049, male, 21.5 mm SL) and live specimens from Yaku-shima island (D: KAUM–I. 163186, female, 36.4 mm SL; E: KAUM–I. 163183, female, 42.3 mm SL). A–C: euthanized before fixation; D, E: living specimens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144866/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144868>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Head of Luciogobius griseus n. sp. (KAUM–I. 154203), showing cephalic sensory system. Black dots, AN and PN indicate papillae, and points of anterior and posterior nostrils, respectively." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144868/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144870>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Fresh specimen of post-flexion larva of Luciogobius griseus n. sp. (KAUM–I. 182447, 13.8 mm SL). Photographs taken before fixation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144870/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144872>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Sexual dimorphism of interorbital space as % of standard length (A) and head length (B) in Luciogobius griseus n. sp. Triangles: males; squares: females; diamonds: sex unknown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144872/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144874>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitats of Luciogobius griseus n. sp. A: Rocky coast of Ambo, Yaku-shima island (red arrow: pool formed by freshwater spring in intertidal zone); B and F: coast around Zatsun River mouth, Okinawa-jima island; C: rocky coast of Imazato, Amami-oshima island (red arrow: freshwater spring in intertidal zone); D: gravel beach of Akirigami, Tokuno-shima island; E: Otoko River mouth, Yaku-shima island." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144874/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144876>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Distribution of species of the Luciogobius platycephalus complex. Stars: L. griseus; circles: L. platycephalus; triangles: Luciogobius sp. 7 sensu Shibukawa et al. (2019). Purple dotted line indicates Osumi line." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144876/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144878>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Relationship of (A) pelvic-fin length (P2F length) as % of pre-dorsal-fin length (PDF) and (B) PDF + P2A length as % of standard length (SL) in the Luciogobius platycephalus complex. Closed star: holotype of L. griseus; open stars: paratypes of L. griseus; circles: non-type specimens of L. platycephalus; triangles: Luciogobius sp. 7 sensu Shibukawa et al. (2019)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144878/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144880>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Relationships of (A) head length, (B) P2A length, (C) pre-dorsal-fin length (PDF), (D) pre-anal-fin length, (E) prepelvic-fin length, and (F) pelvic-fin length (P2F length) as % of standard length (SL) in the Luciogobius platycephalus complex. Closed star: holotype of L. griseus; open stars: paratypes of L. griseus; closed circle: holotype of L. platycephalus; open circles: non-type specimens of L. platycephalus; triangles: Luciogobius sp. 7 sensu Shibukawa et al. (2019)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144880/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144882>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Fresh specimens of Luciogobius platycephalus from Kagoshima Bay (A: KAUM–I. 153354, male, 51.6 mm SL), western coast of Kyushu (B: KAUM–I. 142212, female, 51.5 mm SL; C: KAUM–I. 142238, female, 30.6 mm SL), southeastern coast of Kyushu (D: KAUM–I. 149613, female, 33.6 mm SL), and Tanega-shima island (E: KAUM–I. 146245, female, 26.2 mm SL). Photographs taken immediately after fixation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144882/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10144884>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Fresh specimens of Luciogobius sp. 7 sensu Shibukawa et al. (2019) from Kochi Prefecture, Shikoku, Japan. A: KAUM–I. 159033, male, 51.3 mm SL; B: KAUM–I. 159029, female, 33.2 mm SL; C: KAUM–I. 159028, female, 32.1 mm SL. Photographs taken immediately after fixation." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10144884/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

